{# templates/roadmaps/tax/avoiding-the-wash-sale-rule.html.twig #}
{% extends 'base-roadmaps.html.twig' %}

{% block stylesheets %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_link_tags('tax_css') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block javascripts %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_script_tags('tax_js') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <div class="container">
        <!-- article hero – tax style -->
        <div class="article-hero animate" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e2b37 0%, #2c3e50 100%);">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <div class="hero-icon" style="background-color: var(--tax-smart-color);">
                    <i class="fas fa-broom"></i>
                </div>
                <h1>Avoiding the <span>Wash Sale Rule</span></h1>
                <p class="hero-description">
                    Learn how to harvest tax losses without triggering the IRS wash sale rule. Understand the 30‑day window,
                    what counts as "substantially identical," and strategies to work around the rules while staying compliant.
                </p>
                <div class="phase-tag" style="background-color: rgba(44,62,80,0.2); color: #b0c4de;">
                    <i class="fas fa-layer-group"></i> Phase 2: Risk Management · 8 min read
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- introduction -->
        <section class="animate">
            <h2 class="section-title">📖 The 30‑Day Trap</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                Tax‑loss harvesting can save you money – but only if you avoid the wash sale rule. This IRS rule disallows the tax benefit of a loss if you buy a "substantially identical" security within 30 days before or after the sale. Understanding the rule is essential for any investor who wants to manage taxes effectively.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- key takeaways in rule‑grid style -->
        <div class="rule-grid animate">
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-calendar-alt"></i> The 61‑Day Window</h4>
                <p>The wash sale rule applies if you buy the same or a substantially identical security within 30 days <strong>before or after</strong> the sale. That’s a total of 61 days (the sale day, 30 days before, and 30 days after).</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> "Substantially Identical"</h4>
                <p>Generally, the same stock, a different share class of the same fund, or options/contracts on the same security. ETFs tracking the same index may be considered substantially identical by some interpretations.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> How to Avoid It</h4>
                <p>Wait 31 days before repurchasing, or replace the security with a similar but not "substantially identical" alternative (e.g., swap S&P 500 ETF for Total Market ETF).</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- interactive tool: Wash Sale Rule Checker -->
        <div class="card animate" style="margin: 40px 0;" id="wash-sale-tool">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-calculator"></i> Interactive: Wash Sale Rule Checker</h3>
            <p>Enter a sale date and a repurchase date to see if a wash sale occurs. Use the calendar to pick dates.</p>

            <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;">
                <div style="flex: 1 1 250px;">
                    <label>Sale Date (when you sold at a loss)</label>
                    <input type="date" id="saleDate" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;" value="2024-01-15">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 250px;">
                    <label>Repurchase Date (when you bought the same/similar security)</label>
                    <input type="date" id="repurchaseDate" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;" value="2024-02-10">
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
                <button id="checkWashSale" class="btn-outline">Check for Wash Sale</button>
            </div>

            <div id="washSaleResult" style="margin-top: 25px; padding: 20px; background: var(--light-color); border-radius: 12px;">
                <p>Click the button to see if your transaction triggers a wash sale.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="pro-tip" style="margin-top: 15px; background-color: #eef2f5; border-left-color: var(--tax-smart-color);">
                <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> This tool demonstrates the 61‑day window. In real life, you must also consider purchases made in all accounts (including IRAs) and by your spouse.
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- quiz section (conditional) -->
        {% if app.user and quiz is defined and quiz %}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" style="background: #1e1a3a;">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">🧠 You've already taken this quiz</h3>
                <p style="color: #e2e8f0; font-size: 1.2rem;">
                    Your score: <strong>{{ quiz.quizzScore }}%</strong>
                </p>
                <p style="color: #cbd5e0;">
                    You can retake the quiz to improve your score. Click the button below to reset it.
                </p>
                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'tax', slug: 'avoiding-the-wash-sale-rule', retake: 1 }) }}"
                       class="btn"
                       style="background-color: #2c3e50; color: white; text-decoration: none;">
                        Retake Quiz
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        {% else %}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" data-page-id="{{ page.id }}" style="background: #1e2b37;">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">📝 Test your knowledge: Avoiding the Wash Sale Rule</h3>

                <div class="quiz-question">1. What is the wash sale rule?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="1">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">It disallows a loss deduction if you buy a substantially identical security within 30 days before or after the sale</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">It requires you to hold securities for at least 30 days to claim a loss</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">It prohibits selling securities at a loss</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">It allows you to double‑count losses</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">2. How many days make up the "wash sale window" (including the sale day)?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="2">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">30 days</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">60 days</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">61 days</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">90 days</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">3. Which of the following would likely be considered "substantially identical" to a stock?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="3">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Call options on the same stock</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">A different stock in the same industry</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">A bond issued by the same company</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">A mutual fund that holds many stocks</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">4. If you sell a stock at a loss on December 20, when is the earliest you can repurchase the same stock without triggering a wash sale?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="4">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">December 21</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">January 19</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">January 20</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">January 31</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">5. What happens to the disallowed loss when a wash sale occurs?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="5">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">It is permanently lost</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">It is added to the cost basis of the new shares</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">It can be deducted in the next tax year</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">It becomes a short‑term gain</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <button id="quiz-submit" class="btn" style="background-color: var(--tax-smart-color);">Get score & submit</button>
                </div>
                <div class="quiz-result"></div>
            </div>
        {% endif %}

        <!-- next steps in phase 2 (Risk Management) -->
        <section style="margin: 60px 0;">
            <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: center;">📘 Continue Phase 2: Risk Management</h2>
            <div class="next-steps">
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'tax', slug: 'tax-loss-harvesting' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-leaf"></i>
                    <h3>Tax‑Loss Harvesting</h3>
                    <p>Turn losses into savings – the basics.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'tax', slug: 'asset-location-which-investments-go-where' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-location-dot"></i>
                    <h3>Asset Location</h3>
                    <p>Why holding bonds in taxable accounts can be inefficient.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'tax', slug: 'tax-implications-of-rebalancing' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-arrows-rotate"></i>
                    <h3>Tax Implications of Rebalancing</h3>
                    <p>Smart tactics to rebalance without triggering unnecessary taxes.</p>
                </a>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
